{
  "text": "The nine describe themselves as the nine principles of God. Can you tell me what they mean by that? I am wrong. This is also a veiled statement. The attempt is made to indicate that the nine who sit upon the council are those representing the Creator, the one creator, just as there may be nine witnesses in a courtroom testifying for one defendant. The term principle has this meaning also. The desire of the scribe may be seen in much of this material to have affected the manner of its presentation just as the abilities and preferences of this group determine the nature of this contact. The difference lies in the fact that we are as we are. Thus we may either speak as we will or not speak at all. This demands a very attuned, shall we say, group.",
